# Commenting Rules

## NO Comments Policy
- **NO comments allowed** except for actionable TODOs
- Remove all debugging println statements
- Follow clean code standards - code should be self-documenting
- Only exception: `// TODO: [actionable item]` comments

## Allowed Comments
```kotlin
// TODO: Add input validation for email field
// TODO: Implement rate limiting for this endpoint
// TODO: Add comprehensive error handling
```

## Forbidden Comments
```kotlin
// ❌ Wrong - Explanatory comment
// This function validates user input

// ❌ Wrong - Debugging comment
// println("Debug: user ID is $userId")

// ❌ Wrong - Obvious comment
// Get user by ID
val user = getUserById(id)
```

## Code Self-Documentation
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Write small, focused functions
- Use meaningful class and method names
- Follow Kotlin naming conventions
- Structure code logically

## Clean Code Principles
- Functions should do one thing well
- Variable names should be descriptive
- Code should be readable without comments
- Complex logic should be broken into smaller functions
- Use type-safe programming practices